            corner_defs = [
                ((min_r, min_c), (1, 1)),    # top-left
                ((min_r, max_c), (1, -1)),   # top-right
                ((max_r, min_c), (-1, 1)),   # bottom-left
                ((max_r, max_c), (-1, -1)),  # bottom-right
            ]

            def diagonal_sequence(start_rc, drdc):
                (cr, cc) = start_rc
                (dr, dc) = drdc
                if (cr, cc) not in cellset:
                    cr, cc = min(cells, key=lambda t: abs(t[0] - cr) + abs(t[1] - cc))
                seq = [grid[cr][cc]]
                r, c = cr, cc
                while True:
                    nr, nc = r + dr, c + dc
                    if (nr, nc) not in cellset:
                        break
                    val = grid[nr][nc]
                    if val == comp_bg:
                        break
                    seq.append(val)
                    r, c = nr, nc
                return (cr, cc), seq

            candidates = [diagonal_sequence(corner, drdc) for corner, drdc in corner_defs]
            non_bg_starts = [cand for cand in candidates if cand[1][0] != comp_bg]
            consider = non_bg_starts if non_bg_starts else candidates

            # Choose the corner with the longest diagonal key (tie breaks by order in corner_defs)
            best_seq = consider[0][1]
            best_len = len(best_seq)
            for _, seq in consider[1:]:
                if len(seq) > best_len:
                    best_seq = seq
                    best_len = len(seq)
            cycle = best_seq
            m = len(cycle)

            # Boundary (8-neighbor): any cell touching outside the component in 8 directions
            boundary = set()
            for r, c in cells:
                for dr, dc in dirs8:
                    nr, nc = r + dr, c + dc
                    if nr < 0 or nr >= H or nc < 0 or nc >= W or (nr, nc) not in cellset:
                        boundary.add((r, c))
                        break

            # 8-neighbor BFS distance from boundary
            dist = {}
            dq = deque()
            for bc in boundary:
                dist[bc] = 0
                dq.append(bc)

            while dq:
                r, c = dq.popleft()
                d = dist[(r, c)]
                for dr, dc in dirs8:
                    nr, nc = r + dr, c + dc
                    if (nr, nc) in cellset and (nr, nc) not in dist:
                        dist[(nr, nc)] = d + 1
                        dq.append((nr, nc))

            # Paint component
            for (r, c), d in dist.items():
                out[r][c] = cycle[d % m]

    return out
